Classical swine fever [CSF], Mongolia
-------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 18 Jan 2016 from Dr Bolortuya Purevsuren, OIE delegate, Veterinary and Animal Breeding Agency, Ministry for Industry and Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 20 Oct 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 9 Nov 2015
Date event resolved: 4 Jan 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 7 May 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: classical swine fever virus [CSFV]
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks: 3
Outbreak 1: A pig farm, 1 bag Malchin horoolol, Kherlen soum, Dornod
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Oct 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 16 Nov 2015
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / - / 232 / 22 / 205 / 5

Outbreak 2: A pig farm, Erdenebadrakh bag sansar1, Bayantumen soum, Dornod
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Nov 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 24 Nov 2015
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / - / 24 / 0 / 24 / 0

Outbreak 3: A pig farm, 5 khoroo Gordak zadgai, Nalaikh duureg, Tuv [Tov]
Date of start of the outbreak: 9 Nov 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 4 Jan 2016
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / - / 16 / 16 / 147 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / - / 272 / 38 / 376 / 5
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / ** / ** / 14 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: disinfection/disinfestations; quarantine; stamping out; no treatment of affected animals; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Dornod / swine / 710 / -
Tuv / swine / 4900 / -
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: State Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Swine / antibody detection ELISA / 9 Nov 2015 / Positive
Swine / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 9 Nov 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

