communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Although this event was reported 2 months after its confirmation, it is encouraging to learn that CSF continues to be monitored, and that proper measures for its control are being applied.

In March 2015, classical swine fever was reported in domestic swine in the Province of Tuv (Tov). The event was resolved on 7 May 2015. See event summary at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=17506. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3947033,1.]
